Whereas Fort Huachuca is a product of the Indian Wars in the late 19th century in which Colonel
			 August V. Kautz, commander of the Department of Arizona, ordered that a
			 camp be established in the Huachuca Mountains in February 1877;

Whereas in the 1930s, the 25th Infantry Regiment replaced the 10th Calvary in Fort Huachuca and
			 eventually sent up to 30,000 troops to fight in the European theater of
			 World War II;

